Case 2: Legal hallucination  
In a well-known case, a lawyer used an AI system to generate legal references for a court case. The AI produced citations of cases that did not actually exist. The lawyer submitted these references, and the court later discovered they were completely fabricated.  
This shows that AI can generate highly realistic but false information, which can lead to serious consequences in professional settings.
https://hai.stanford.edu/news/ai-trial-legal-models-hallucinate-1-out-6-or-more-benchmarking-queries?utm_source=chatgpt.com

These examples demonstrate that AI systems can produce convincing but incorrect information. Therefore, users must verify AI-generated content, especially in critical areas such as healthcare and law.
